cs.SD, cs.SI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.AI

Reasoning: 
- cs.SD (Sound): The paper deals with distances on symbolic musical sequences, which can be considered as a type of sound data. 
- cs.SI (Signal Processing): The paper proposes a method to build a distance that is invariant under transpositions, which can be seen as a signal processing problem. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning): The paper uses a hybrid distance that combines learned feature representations with a handcrafted rank distance, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval): The paper mentions music retrieval as one of the applications that require distances on musical sequences. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper proposes a method to build a distance on musical sequences that takes into account the style of the corpus, which can be seen as an AI problem.
